      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RACHELS LEGACY (9) comes through the Nutrien Classic Sales race series where she was runner-up in the heats before finishing fourth in the final at Listed level. Overcame a wide barrier to win at this circuit and distance prior to that series. Draws for a trail and looks well placed. YIRRADIVA (7) looks close to a win after back-to-back placings. Came from this barrier when she missed by 3m at Bathurst two back then drew on the back row and worked to find the front before sticking on for second at this circuit and distance last week. With even luck she could break through. APPLAUDING (8) draws wide but didn't do a bad job when sixth at Menangle last time out and was an easy Canberra winner three back. KEAYANG DREAMGIRL (6) is lightly-raced with upside and could progress off last week's fresh placing.",
